# Architecture Boundaries

- Keep routing thin: handlers validate input, call domain logic, and shape HTTP responses.
- Keep provider-specific logic in `backend/app/adapters/` only.
- Keep persistence concerns in database/repository functions, not in routers.
- Keep frontend/backend contract types aligned with shared schema definitions.

## Required Patterns

- Routers call services/adapters; they do not contain business workflows.
- Adapters return normalized response models, not provider-native payloads.
- Shared behavior should extend existing modules before adding new abstractions.
- New providers must follow the adapter registry pattern already used in this codebase.

## Prohibited Patterns

- No direct provider SDK calls from `backend/app/routers/`.
- No raw SQL or DB session orchestration in route handlers.
- No leaking provider-specific fields through API responses.
- No contract-breaking endpoint or event shape changes without explicit approval.
